---
# Optional per-project settings for the saas-startup-team plugin.
# Copy to `.claude/saas-startup-team.local.md` in your product repo and edit.
# All keys are optional; sensible defaults apply when omitted.

# --- Regression-test gate (scripts/check-regression-test.sh) ---
# Which issue labels mark a "must have a regression test" incident. The gate
# only blocks `gh pr merge` when the PR closes an issue carrying one of these.
# Comma-separated. Default:
incident_labels: bug,monitor,customer-issue

# POSIX extended-regex matched against `gh pr diff --name-only` to decide
# whether the diff includes a test. Override for non-JS/Python stacks.
# Default matches: *.test.* *.spec.* test_*.py *_test.go tests/ test/ __tests__/ spec/
# test_path_regex: '(\.test\.|\.spec\.|(^|/)test_[^/]*\.py$|_test\.go$|(^|/)tests?/|(^|/)__tests__/|(^|/)spec/)'

# --- Nightly monitor (/monitor-nightly, scripts/monitor-dedup.sh) ---
# All optional. Defaults shown. repro_recipe is single-line; {entity} is substituted.
monitor:
  repo: owner/name                          # default: resolved via `gh repo view`
  labels: [monitor, customer-issue]         # base labels; the finding's severity is appended
  marker_dir: .monitor
  state_file: .startup/monitor-state.json
  custom_checks: .startup/monitor-checks.sh
  # repro_recipe: ssh <readonly-host> "session-tar {entity}"
---

# saas-startup-team — project settings

This file configures the regression-test gate. The gate blocks `gh pr merge`
for a PR that resolves an incident-labeled GitHub issue (or carries a
`Plane-Item:` marker in its body) unless the diff adds a test, or the PR body
records an override: `Regression-Test: none — <reason>`.
